-- India Raises Nuclear Power Spending 18% to 66.1 Billion Rupees
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2012-03-16T11:27:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/india-raises-nuclear-power-spending-18-to-66-1-billion-rupees.html
India ’s government proposes to
increase spending on nuclear power projects by 18 percent to
66.1 billion rupees ($1.3 billion) in the year starting April 1.  The provision includes equity investment in  Bharatiya
Nabhikiya Vidyut Nigam Ltd. , a unit of the state-owned monopoly
Nuclear Power Corp., according to  budget documents  posted online
by the Ministry of Finance.  The government allocated 140 million rupees for the
Kudankulam nuclear plant in the southern state of Tamil Nadu,
being built with Russia’s help, according to the document.
Protests by villagers have stalled work at the project.  India earmarked 55.8 billion rupees for nuclear projects in
the year ending March 31, the government said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
